705810f-a.title: Brooklyn: Myrtle Avenue - Carlton Avenue
705810f-a.text:
Myrtle Avenue, north side, east from Carlton Avenue to Adelphi Street, seen from underneath the Myrtle Avenue 'El.~
October 10, 1940
705810f-a.folder: Myrtle Avenue & Carlton Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

705813f-a.title: Brooklyn: Myrtle Avenue - Carlton Avenue
705813f-a.text:
Myrtle Avenue (foreground), at the N.W. corner of Carlton Avenue--the latter being on the right--seen from underneath the Myrtle Avenue elevated. All the houses seen in this view were later raed to make way for the
erection of Fort Greene Houses.
October 10, 1940
P. L. Sperr
705813f-a.folder: Myrtle Avenue & Carlton Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

705811f-b.title: Brooklyn: Myrtle Avenue - Carlton Avenue
705811f-b.text:
Myrtle Avenue, north side, west fron. Carlton Avenue, Ehowwing the vast area where Fort Greene Pouses, a low-rent gOvernment housing center, will be erected. In the center background is the New Cumberland Hospital. On tbe left (view 2) is St. Edwards Homan
Cathelic -hurch.
P. L. 3perr  April 22, 1941
NO REPRODUCTIOS  Views 1,2,3
